# LaTeX Application Documents

- CV outputs live at `cv/main_<company>.tex` and should compile with `lualatex` to exactly 2 pages.
- Cover letters live at `cover_letters/cover_<company>_<role>.tex` and should compile with `xelatex` to exactly 1 page.
- Compile and visually inspect PDFs before presenting final files. The `.tex` source alone is not enough.
- Prevent orphaned `\cventry` titles with `\needspace{5\baselineskip}` before entries when needed.
- Use relevance-weighted cutting when content overflows: role relevance, uniqueness, and narrative dependency beat static section trimming.
- For cover-letter bullet lists, do not put `itemize` directly inside `\lettercontent{}`; preserve the Raleway font wrapper described in the cover-letter reference.
- If `pdftotext` is available, verify the CV text layer and keyword coverage from the extracted text.
